name: AddressDictator
description: AddressDictator. The AddressDictator (glory to Arstotzka) is a contract that allows us to safely manipulate many different addresses in the AddressManager without transferring ownership of the AddressManager to a hot wallet or hardware wallet.

functionDecorators.name: returnOwnership
functionDecorators.description: Transfers ownership of this contract to the finalOwner. Only callable by the Final Owner, which is intended to be our multisig. This function shouldn't be necessary, but it gives a sense of reassurance that we can recover if something really surprising goes wrong.

functionDecorators.name: setAddresses
functionDecorators.description: Called to finalize the transfer, this function is callable by anyone, but will only result in an upgrade if this contract is the owner Address Manager.
